<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF81EF42FF42FDDFFDFBFD48" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF81EF42FF42FDDFFE9CFD74" blockId="41.[151,1436,545,753]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF81EF42FF42FDDFFEE7FD3C" bold="true" box="[199,338,618,644]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Comments:</emphasis>
This is the most austral record of the species, moving its known distribution 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF81EF42FB3EFDDEFB68FD3C" box="[1211,1245,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">ca.</emphasis>
<quantity id="9A3CA18EFF81EF42FB61FDDFFAFAFD3C" box="[1252,1359,618,644]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" unit="km" value="3000.0">3,000 km</quantity>
southwards. After its original description, the species was recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF81EF42FCE8FD3BFC79FD10" box="[877,972,654,680]" name="Suriname" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Surinam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFF81EF42FC5FFD3BFB20FD10" author="Naskrecki, P." box="[986,1173,654,680]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="104 - 109" refId="ref34756" refString="Naskrecki, P. (2011) A rapid biological assessment of katydids of the Kwamalasamutu region, Suriname (Insecta: Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae). Bulletin of Biological Assessment, 63, 104 - 109." type="journal article" year="2011">Naskrecki, 2011</bibRefCitation>
) and now in the 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF81EF42FAD5FD3BFF67FD74" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Paraná State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF81EF42FF58FD07FE90FD74" box="[221,293,690,716]" name="Brazil" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF81EF42FF42FD63FDFBFD48" blockId="41.[151,1436,545,753]" box="[199,590,726,753]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF81EF42FF42FD63FED1FD48" bold="true" box="[199,356,726,752]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Bioacoustics:</emphasis>
